  "text": "In Kubernetes, API group storage version registration mapping v1beta1 to v1 equivalents is handled through several key components found in the kubernetes/kubernetes repository.\n\n## REST Storage Providers\n\nMultiple REST storage providers in `pkg/registry/*/rest/storage_*.go` define methods for registering different API versions. The primary files implementing storage version registration are:\n\n### Files with v1beta1 to v1 Mapping\n\n1. **pkg/registry/authentication/rest/storage_authentication.go** - Implements `RESTStorageProvider` with methods for `v1alpha1Storage()`, `v1beta1Storage()`, and `v1Storage()`. These methods register different versions of the authentication API.\n\n2. **pkg/registry/storage/rest/storage_storage.go** - Contains `RESTStorageProvider` implementing storage versions for the storage API group with `v1alpha1Storage()`, `v1beta1Storage()`, and `v1Storage()` methods.\n\n3. **pkg/registry/admissionregistration/rest/storage_apiserver.go** - Implements `RESTStorageProvider` with all three storage version methods (`v1alpha1Storage()`, `v1beta1Storage()`, `v1Storage()`) to register admission registration policies at different API versions.\n\n4. **pkg/registry/resource/rest/storage_resource.go** - Implements `RESTStorageProvider` with `v1alpha3Storage()` and `v1beta1Storage()` methods for the resource API group (Dynamic Resource Allocation).\n\n### Additional Storage Providers\n\nOther REST storage providers with single or dual version support:\n- **pkg/registry/networking/rest/storage_settings.go** - `v1alpha1Storage()` and `v1Storage()`\n- **pkg/registry/certificates/rest/storage_certificates.go** - `v1alpha1Storage()` and `v1Storage()`\n- **pkg/registry/apiserverinternal/rest/storage.go** - `v1alpha1Storage()` only\n- **pkg/registry/discovery/rest/storage_discovery.go**, **pkg/registry/events/rest/storage_events.go**, and others - `v1Storage()` only\n\n## StorageVersion Manager Interface\n\nThe **staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storageversion/manager.go** file defines the `Manager` interface (line 54) that records which resources need storage version updates and provides methods for:\n\n- `AddResourceInfo()` - Records resources whose StorageVersions need updates\n- `UpdateStorageVersions()` - Updates StorageVersions of recorded resources in etcd\n- `PendingUpdate()` - Checks if a resource's StorageVersion update is pending\n- `LastUpdateError()` - Returns the last error for a resource's update\n- `Completed()` - Returns whether all updates are complete\n\nThe `defaultManager` struct (line 70) implements this interface and maintains resource-to-StorageVersion mappings.\n\n## ResourceEncodingConfig Interface\n\nThe **staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/server/storage/resource_encoding_config.go** file defines:\n\n1. **ResourceEncodingConfig interface** (line 28) - Determines which GroupVersion is used for etcd storage:\n   - `StorageEncodingFor()` - Returns the serialization format (GroupVersion) for storing a resource\n   - `InMemoryEncodingFor()` - Returns the in-memory representation encoding\n\n2. **DefaultResourceEncodingConfig struct** (line 42) - Implements the interface with:\n   - `resources` map storing overriding encoding configs per GroupResource\n   - `SetResourceEncoding()` - Sets custom storage encoding for specific resources\n   - `StorageEncodingFor()` - Returns the external storage encoding version\n   - `InMemoryEncodingFor()` - Returns the internal storage encoding version\n\nThis config allows explicit mapping of v1beta1 resources to their v1 equivalents for etcd storage while maintaining backward compatibility for decoding multiple versions.\n\n## Integration Pattern\n\nThe pattern followed across all storage providers is:\n1. Each API group has a `RESTStorageProvider` (or `StorageProvider`) struct in its rest package\n2. The provider implements separate `v1Storage()`, `v1beta1Storage()`, and optionally `v1alpha1Storage()` methods\n3. `NewRESTStorage()` calls each version's method and populates `VersionedResourcesStorageMap` in the `APIGroupInfo`\n4. The `ResourceEncodingConfig` determines which version is actually used for etcd persistence\n5. The `StorageVersion` Manager tracks which versions are being used and updates the StorageVersion API objects accordingly\n\nThis architecture enables Kubernetes to serve multiple API versions (v1, v1beta1, v1alpha1, etc.) while using a single underlying storage version in etcd, with automatic conversion between formats as needed."
}

